    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>This plugin simply expands the tabs in the single-product page. It will remove the tabs (Description, Reviews or other custom tabs) and show only the content of the tabs one after another.<\/p>\n<p>You can enable the tabs expansion only for desktop or only for mobile devices. Check the settings on the Woocommerce-&gt;Settings-&gt;Products-&gt;Display page, as shown in the <a href=\"https:\/\/ps.w.org\/woocommerce-extend-tabs\/assets\/screenshot-2.png\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">screenshot<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>The plugin supports WooCommerce tabs added by other plugins. The content of all of your tabs will be shown one section after another.<\/p>\n<p>If you liked this plugin, feel free to play around with our other free plugins: <a href=\"https:\/\/wordpress.org\/plugins\/custom-css-js\/\" rel=\"ugc\">Simple Custom CSS &amp; JS<\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/wordpress.org\/plugins\/wp-multi-step-checkout\/\" rel=\"ugc\">WooCommerce Multi-Step Checkout<\/a>.<\/p>\n",
        "installation": "<h4>Automatic installation<\/h4>\n<ol>\n<li>Press <strong>Install<\/strong> to install this plugin to your WordPress.<\/li>\n<li>Enable the plugin in WP admin.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<h4>Manual installation<\/h4>\n<ol>\n<li>Download <code>woocommerce-extend-tabs.zip<\/code> from any available source.<\/li>\n<li>Connect to your FTP server and upload and extract the zip-archive to your <code>\/wp-content\/plugins\/<\/code> folder.<\/li>\n<li>Enable the plugin in WP admin.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n",
        "faq": "\n<dt id='with%20which%20woocommerce%20versions%20is%20the%20plugin%20compatible%3F'>\nWith which WooCommerce versions is the plugin compatible?\n<\/h4>\n<p>\n<p>The plugin works with WooCommerce from 2.1 to up the latest 6.8 version.<\/p>\n<\/p>\n<dt id='why%20aren%27t%20the%20titles%20of%20the%20tabs%20shown%20on%20my%20site%3F'>\nWhy aren&#8217;t the titles of the tabs shown on my site?\n<\/h4>\n<p>\n<p>Some themes suppress the <code>&lt;h2&gt;<\/code> title of the section with CSS or by overwritting the template file. We tested the plugin on 22 free themes that support WooCommerce and on two of them the <code>&lt;h2&gt;<\/code> title was hidden. This plugin should work for most of the themes, but we take no responsability for the themes that don&#8217;t show the <code>&lt;h2&gt;<\/code> title of the section.<\/p>\n<\/p>\n<dt id='does%20it%20support%20tabs%20created%20by%20other%20plugins%3F'>\nDoes it support tabs created by other plugins?\n<\/h4>\n<p>\n<p>Yes<\/p>\n<\/p>\n<dt id='does%20it%20support%20multi-site%20wordpress%20installations%3F'>\nDoes it support multi-site WordPress installations?\n<\/h4>\n<p>\n<p>Yes<\/p>\n<\/p>\n<dt id='i%20want%20to%20add%2Fmodify%2Fdelete%20a%20tab'>\nI want to add\/modify\/delete a tab\n<\/h4>\n<p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re comfortable with adding code to your website, then see the <a href=\"https:\/\/docs.woocommerce.com\/document\/editing-product-data-tabs\/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">WooCommerce documentation<\/a>. If not, you can check out a plugin similar to <a href=\"https:\/\/docs.woocommerce.com\/document\/tab-manager\/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">WooCommerce Tab Manager<\/a>.<\/p>\n<\/p>\n<dt id='why%20doesn%27t%20it%20work%20on%20my%20website%3F'>\nWhy doesn&#8217;t it work on my website?\n<\/h4>\n<p>\n<p>We are aware only of an incompatibility with the Digi theme by Nasa. For other issues than that drop me a line in the support and maybe we can try to figure it out.<\/p>\n<\/p>\n\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>1.27<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Compatibility with WC8.5<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.26<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix: Load the woo-single-prod-el-reviews.min.css file if the WoodMart theme is active.<\/li>\n<li>Compatibility with the WooCommerce &#8220;Custom Order Tables&#8221; feature<\/li>\n<li>Compatibility with WC7.8<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.25<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Compatibility with WC7.2<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.24<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix: limit the Flatsome theme rules only to the WooCommerce pages <\/li>\n<li>Compatibility with WC6.8<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.23<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Compatibility with WC6.4<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.22<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Compatibility with WC6.1<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.21<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Compatibility with WC5.6<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.20<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Compatibility with WC5.3<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.19<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Compatibility with the WoodMart theme<\/li>\n<li>Compatibility with WC5.0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.18<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Compatibility with WC4.5<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.17<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Compatibility with WC4.4<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.16<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Compatibility with WC4.2 and WC4.3<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.15<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Compatibility with WC4.1<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.14<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Compatibility with WC4.0<\/li>\n<li>Compatibility with WP5.4<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.13<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Compatibility with WC3.9<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.12<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Declare compatibility with WC3.8<\/li>\n<li>Add <code>woocommerce_product_after_tabs<\/code> hook in the tabs template for WC3.8<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.11<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix: laod the unminified JS if the SCRIPT_DEBUG constant is defined<\/li>\n<li>Declare compatibility with WP 5.3<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.10<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Update: make the code compatible with WC 3.6<\/li>\n<li>Declare compatibility with WC 3.6<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.9<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Declare compatibility WordPress 5.0 and WooCommerce 3.5<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.8<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Use a different single-product.js file for every WooCommerce minor release <\/li>\n<li>Remove the donation link<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.7<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Update: make the code compatible with WC 3.2<\/li>\n<li>Declare compatibility with WooCommerce 3.2 (https:\/\/woocommerce.wordpress.com\/2017\/08\/28\/new-version-check-in-woocommerce-3-2\/)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.6<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix: again https:\/\/wordpress.org\/support\/topic\/bug-with-enfold-theme\/<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.5<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix: https:\/\/wordpress.org\/support\/topic\/bug-with-enfold-theme\/<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.4<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Update: make the code compatible with WooCommerce 3.0.+ <\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.3<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix: PHP warning for Additional Tabs without weight, dimensions or attributes as explained in https:\/\/docs.woocommerce.com\/document\/editing-product-data-tabs\/#section-6<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.2<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Feature: compatibility with the Enfold theme<\/li>\n<li>Feature: compatibility with the Flatsome theme<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.1.1<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix: adjusted the single-product.js file to the WooCommerce 2.5.2 version<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.1.0<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix: Error &#8220;Call to undefined function wp_is_mobile&#8221; on multi-site installations<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.0.4<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added the &#8216;Enable for desktop devices&#8217; and &#8216;Enable for mobile devices&#8217; options<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.0.3<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Bug: https:\/\/wordpress.org\/support\/topic\/warning-missing-argument-1-for-woocommerce_output_product_data_tabs-see-mor<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.0.2<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Tweak: support up to WordPress 4.2.1<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.0.1<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Change readme.txt file to show the screenshots on wordpress.org<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.0.0<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Initial release of WooCommerce Expand Tabs<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n",
        "screenshots": "<ol><li><a href=\"https:\/\/ps.w.org\/woocommerce-extend-tabs\/assets\/screenshot-1.png?rev=2298448\"><img src=\"https:\/\/ps.w.org\/woocommerce-extend-tabs\/assets\/screenshot-1.png?rev=2298448\" alt=\"Example of tabs expanded on the OceanWP theme\"><\/a><p>Example of tabs expanded on the OceanWP theme<\/p><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/ps.w.org\/woocommerce-extend-tabs\/assets\/screenshot-2.png?rev=2298448\"><img src=\"https:\/\/ps.w.org\/woocommerce-extend-tabs\/assets\/screenshot-2.png?rev=2298448\" alt=\"Settings for enabling\/disabling the tabs expansion\"><\/a><p>Settings for enabling\/disabling the tabs expansion<\/p><\/li><\/ol>",
        "reviews": "<div class=\"review\">\n\t<div class=\"review-head\">\n\t\t<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n\t\t\t\t<h4 class=\"review-title\">Great plugin<\/h4>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"star-rating\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><\/div>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<p class=\"reviewer\">\n\t\t\t\tBy <a href=\"https:\/\/profiles.wordpress.org\/theo10\/\"><img alt='' src='https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/8a97b6cab6f6cf3ed227a96dbb2cbd62?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g' srcset='https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/8a97b6cab6f6cf3ed227a96dbb2cbd62?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-16 photo' height='16' width='16' loading='lazy' decoding='async'\/><\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/profiles.wordpress.org\/theo10\/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">theo10<\/a> on <span class=\"review-date\">August 20, 2022<\/span>\t\t\t<\/p>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t<\/div>\n\t<div class=\"review-body\">This plugin is amazing. The only problem is the additional code does not work to show the tab titles.<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n\t<div class=\"review-head\">\n\t\t<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n\t\t\t\t<h4 class=\"review-title\">Awesome Plugin<\/h4>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"star-rating\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/sp